CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 15, 1962, pg. 2 reads: "Thinkers - Among guests at Sunday's 'Operation Think' meeting at Westray Plaza were, left to right, standing: An unidentified guardsman, James Sanford, Luther Sewell, Harold Keith, Bill Carter, John Sinclair, Wendell Freeland and W.P. Young. Seated at table: Mrs. Minona Clinton, Councilman James A. Jordon, Johnny Wheeler and Bill Paige.  Seated below the platform are Harold McClain, Cal Spittler, Charles E. Pendleton, James Edmonds, Ed Bryant, Ernest O'Connor Jr., Curtis Hefflin, Thurston (Ducky) Lane, Robert Ficklin and Oscar Buckner. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, standing from left: unknown man, James Sanford, Luther Sewell, Harold Keith, Bill Carter, John Sinclair, Weldell Freeland, W. P. Young; seated at table: Minona Clinton, James A. Jordon, Johnny Wheeler, Bill Paige; seated below platform: Harold McClain, Cal Spittler, Charles E. Pendleton, James Edmonds, Ed Bryant, Ernest O'Connor Jr., Curtis Hefflin, Thurston "Ducky" Lane, Robert Ficklin, and Oscar Buckner, gathered in Westray Plaza for Operation Think meeting
